# VIGIL APEX Tor v3 hidden service for the public tip portal.
#
# Per THREAT-MODEL-CMR §02: tippers in adversarial regions need a path
# that cannot be observed by upstream ISPs. The .onion address is shown
# inline on the /tip page (and in printed materials handed out by
# civil-society partners). The same Caddy backend serves both clearnet
# and onion — Tor terminates here and forwards to vigil-caddy:80.

User vigil-tor
DataDirectory /var/lib/tor
SocksPort 0
ControlPort 0

# v3 hidden service. Key material is generated on first run and kept
# under /var/lib/tor/vigil-tip — this directory MUST be on encrypted
# storage (it is on /srv/vigil/* which is on the LUKS-backed Btrfs
# subvol, per W-12) and backed up via vigil-backup.
HiddenServiceDir /var/lib/tor/vigil-tip
HiddenServicePort 80 vigil-caddy:80
HiddenServiceVersion 3
HiddenServicePoWDefensesEnabled 1

# Don't run as a relay — outbound traffic only when fetching descriptors.
ClientOnly 0

Log notice stdout
